<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-10-03T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-10-03T15:00:00-05:00" n="151" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d151">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72114A/206</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_WJE1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Willard</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-10-03T16:00:00-04:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">October 3, 1918, 4 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1629. Your 1871, October 1, 1 p.m. Department instructs you to
                            communicate direct with <persName corresp="#p_GJW1">Garrett</persName>
                            relative to the date of the Austro-Hungarian conference and then to
                            communicate his reply to the Austro-Hungarian Government through the
                            proper channels, keeping the Department advised as to the date thus
                            agreed upon.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>